  "prompt": "Is it necessary to complete graduation to get the software engineering job at Google?",
  "response": "While having a degree in computer science or a related field can be beneficial for a career in software engineering at Google, it is not strictly necessary. Google, like many tech companies, focuses on skills and abilities rather than just formal education. They often look for candidates who can demonstrate strong programming skills, problem-solving abilities, and relevant experience.\n\nGoogle has been known to hire individuals without a traditional degree if they have proven expertise, such as through coding bootcamps, project work, contributions to open source, or professional experience. The interview process at Google is rigorous, usually involving technical assessments and coding interviews, during which practical skills are more critical than formal qualifications.\n\nIf you're aiming for a software engineering position at Google without a degree, it's important to build a strong portfolio, gain experience through internships or personal projects, and continuously develop your skills in programming and software development.",
